This paper deals with transfer reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a method to obtain causal bounds on the transition and reward functions, which is related to causal inference and causal reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also provides numerical experiments for robot motion planning problems, which further supports the relevance of cs.RO. Additionally, the paper proposes new Q learning and UCB-Q learning algorithms, which are related to control engineering, and thus cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with contextual information, which is related to human-computer interaction and user modeling, and thus cs.CE (Computers and Society) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
